14.7 . For the purposes of this Agreement, "" shall mean breaches of Seller's representations, warranties, covenants, indemnities or other obligations which (i) are not, individually, de minimis and (ii) would result in Purchaser incurring actual out-of-pocket damages and expenses relating directly to such breaches in excess of ONE HUNDRED THOUSAND AND NO/100 DOLLARS ($100,000.00) in the aggregate. Any breach which, individually, results in damages or expenses of not more than $5,000, shall be considered de minimis (a ). De Minimis Breaches shall not be included among Seller's Post-Closing Representation Liabilities (as defined below) or be included in or
Limitation on Liability
