that the foregoing shall not excuse the L/C Issuer from liability to the Borrower or any of its Subsidiaries to the extent of direct damages (as opposed to special, indirect, consequential or punitive damages) suffered by the Borrower or any of its Subsidiaries that are determined in a final, nonappealable judgment by a court of competent jurisdiction to have resulted from the L/C Issuer's bad faith, gross negligence or willful misconduct.
